EXTENDED OUTLOOK
FRIDAY TO MONDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 062300 UTC
DURING FRIDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL LIE ACROSS THE BRITISH
ISLES THEN DECLINE EWARDS INTO THE N SEA THROUGH SATURDAY MORNING. A SMALL
LOW CENTRE WILL LIE IN THE SERN N SEA DURING FRIDAY EVENING. AN ATLANTIC
LOW PRESSURE AREA 979 SW OF ICELAND AT FIRST WILL EXTEND A FRONTAL TROUGH
TOWARDS THE UK THROUGH SATURDAY WITH A SECONDARY LOW PRESSURE AREA FORMING
OVER BRITAIN LATER IN THE DAY. A SIMILAR CYCLONIC PATTERN WILL PERSIST THROUGH
SUNDAY AND MONDAY WITH DEEP LOW PRESSURE SW OR S OF ICELAND AND ACTIVE FRONTAL
TROUGHS RUNNING ACROSS BRITAIN AND IRELAND INTO THE N SEA. DURING FRIDAY
EVENING AND SATURDAY WINDS WILL BE STRG TO GALE IN ATLANTIC SEA AREAS AND
LUNDY AND IRISH SEA. ON SUNDAY AND MONDAY FURTHER STRG WINDS OR GALES ARE
EXP WITH POSS SEV GALES OR STORMS IN SHANNON ROCKALL AND SE ICELAND ON
